<table width="95%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="2" align="center" bgcolor="#000000">
<tr><td class="newsheader"><a href="/profiles/detail.php?id=1761" class="newsheader">Cristelmoon Soulstealer </a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="newsbody">
<table width='100%' border='0' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5' align='center' class="newsbody">
<tr>
<td valign="top">Level 65 Dark Elf Shadowknight<br>
of RedSky<br><br>The "testing" had gone on for days, supplicants to Innoruuk's church were forced to undergo grueling mental and physical torture before being allowed to become a Shadow Knight. Shadow Knights were the living embodiment of Innoruuk's will on Norath, skilled in the use of arms and necromancy. They must embody both his cruelty and his hate. The testing for Cristelmoon was administered by Canon Terjon, a dark priest of the church with a taste for torture. He came to her daily with new and more vile tortures each time. She thought she would die in his dungeons, away from all who could hear her screams. She prayed to Innoruuk to give her strength to survive, and to endure. Terjon Laughed, "Innoruuk hears not your cries frail girl! He cannot hear the cries of weaklings who crumble from such small pains." No, she thought my lord and master will protect my life and soul. She blacked out then, as the searing brand caressed her flesh again, in her unconsious state she could hear the foul laughter of the priest. Her mind drifted to thoughts of her lord Innoruuk, she saw him sitting in judgement over her, she beseeched his aid and he laughed, laughed! cruelly and harshly. His face changed to that of the priest Terjon and he spoke in a terrible voice. "Foolish child, I come not to save those who are weak, only the strong last in my service. The rest are only fit to be used and devoured!" She was cast out screaming, his mocking laughter ringing in her ears. When she awoke the priest Terjon was still nearby, he was preparing his whips for use. She knew then that only one way lay before her-life or death. As the priest approached, she fiegned unconsiousness. "Perhaps this will arouse you from your peaceful slumbers." As he drew closer she kicked out with a foot sending him sprawling across her form. She grabbed him and her hands sought his scrawny neck. She growled her hatred at him, and began to choke the life from him. He sqawked in suprise and sudden fear. He grabbed at her hands to tear them away and in a maddened state she bit off the finger of his closet hand. He screamed in pain and pleasure was all she felt. She began to see him for the weak and cowardly being he was. He did not deserve to live, How dare he ever have thought to judge her! He tried to escape but her stength was too much, she leaned close to him whispering, "Lord Innoruuk will devour your soul for the weakness you have shown." She eased her deathgrip on his throat and kissed him roughly, once, then bit deeply into his lips. Savoring the taste of the blood and the screams of pain. She felt a strange power in her body, a feeling that could only be the blessing of Innoruuk. Invoking his name and touching the forhead of the priest, a wave of energy coursed through her and into his body. The energy returned back to her, revitalizing her and drawing the remain life from the body of Terjon. A withered corpse fell to the floor. She unlocked her shackles, her stength returned to her. No longer did she feel any trace of weakness. She was stronger physically and spiritually, she now knew her place and would teach others their rightful place at Innoruuk's feet.<br><Br>
<a href="/profiles/detail.php?id=1761" class="smallcomments">Click here to view details about Cristelmoon Soulstealer </a>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
